()CertificationManager kya hai?
--🔹 1️⃣ CertificationManager kya hai?
CertificationManager = wo object ya banda jo certification process ka controller / manager hota hai.
Ye ensure karta hai ki:
Certification campaign (Certification) sahi tarah se run ho
Reviewers aur entities assign ho rahe hain
Status aur escalation rules properly follow ho rahe hain.

🔹 2️⃣ CertificationManager ka kaam:-
()Flow control:-
Decide karta hai kaunse reviewers kaunse entities ko review karenge
()Escalation handling:-
Agar reviewer time me decision na le → escalate to next level
()Notifications:-
Reviewers ko remind karna, campaign start/end alerts
()Metrics & Reporting:-
Kaun entity complete hua, kaun pending, aggregate stats.

3️⃣ Usage Example:-
Agar ek company ke 5 employees ke training scores hain: [70, 80, 90, 100, 85]
Count = 5
Sum = 70+80+90+100+85 = 425
Average = 425 ÷ 5 = 85
Min = 70
Max = 100
Ye sab aggregate stats ke examples hain.

1️⃣ Common Aggregate Stats Methods in CertificationManager:-
Method	                            Kya karta hai	                       Example Output
getTotalCertifications()	Total certifications available	                     50
getCompletedCount()	       Kitne certifications complete ho chuke	             35
getPendingCount()	       Kitne certifications pending hain	                 15
getApprovedCount()	       Total approved certification items	                 30
getRevokedCount()	        Total revoked certification items	                  5
getCompletionPercentage()	Overall % of completed certifications	             70%

2️⃣ Usage Example (Pseudo-code):-
CertificationManager manager = new CertificationManager();
int total = manager.getTotalCertifications();
int completed = manager.getCompletedCount();
int pending = manager.getPendingCount();
int approved = manager.getApprovedCount();
int revoked = manager.getRevokedCount();
double completionPercent = manager.getCompletionPercentage();

System.out.println("Total: " + total);
System.out.println("Completed: " + completed);
System.out.println("Pending: " + pending);
System.out.println("Approved: " + approved);
System.out.println("Revoked: " + revoked);
System.out.println("Completion %: " + completionPercent);

Output Example:-
Total: 50
Completed: 35
Pending: 15
Approved: 30
Revoked: 5
Completion %: 70.0

🔹 3️⃣ CertificationManager ke andar kya hota hai?
Field/Attribute	                         Description
id	                           Unique ID of CertificationManager
name	                          Name / label of manager
assignedCertifications	      List of Certifications ye manager monitor kar raha hai
reviewers	                         List of assigned reviewers
status	                             Active / Inactive / Paused
escalationRules	                     Rules for pending reviews
createdDate	                             Kab create hua
modifiedDate	                       Last modified date

